In this letter, President Barack Obama provides a report on military operations conducted by the United States Armed Forces in support of U.S. counterterrorism objectives and other regional security operations. The report covers various countries and regions, including Afghanistan, Iraq, Syria, Somalia, Yemen, Djibouti, Cuba, Niger, Egypt, Jordan, Kosovo, and Yemen. The President highlights the success in degrading al-Qa'ida's capabilities and bringing an end to the Taliban's rule in Afghanistan. He also mentions the ongoing efforts to combat the Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant (ISIL) in Iraq and Syria. The letter emphasizes the President's authority as Commander in Chief and Chief Executive to conduct these military operations.